1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,600
Not all volcanoes erupt the same way—what's the secret?

2
00:00:03,600 --> 00:00:08,400
Shield volcanoes have gentle slopes, formed by low-viscosity lava that flows easily.

3
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:10,400
Think Mauna Loa in Hawaii.

4
00:00:10,400 --> 00:00:12,000
Stratovolcanoes, like Mount St.

5
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:16,800
Helens, are steeper and more explosive, due to thicker, more viscous lava.

6
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:22,800
This viscosity affects eruption style: shield volcanoes erupt gently, while stratovolcanoes can have catastrophic explosions.

7
00:00:22,800 --> 00:00:24,800
So, shape follows lava chemistry!

8
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:28,800
Understanding this can unlock the mysteries of our planet's forces.

